{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "ea514026459d14ed", "candidate": {"id": "cand-003", "name": "Amara Osei", "raw_cv": "AMARA OSEI\namara.osei@email.com | Remote (based in Accra, Ghana)\n\nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nStrategic product manager with 7 years of experience leading B2B SaaS products from 0 to 1 and through scaling phases. Deep expertise in workflow automation and enterprise procurement software. Experienced people manager with a track record of building high-performing PM teams.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Product Manager \u2014 Coupa Software (Remote) (2021\u2013present)\n- Own the supplier management product line with 3 direct PM reports\n- Drove 35% increase in supplier onboarding completion rate through a redesigned onboarding flow\n- Partnered with enterprise sales to scope and deliver custom integrations for Fortune 500 customers\n- Defined and shipped OKR-aligned roadmaps across 4 engineering squads\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Procurify (Remote) (2019\u20132021)\n- Led product for the approval workflow module; shipped 12 major features in 18 months\n- Worked closely with customer success to reduce churn through targeted product improvements\n- Introduced product analytics (Amplitude) and built a data-driven prioritisation framework\n\nAssociate PM \u2014 Zoho Corporation (Chennai, India) (2017\u20132019)\n- Supported delivery of features for Zoho Books and Zoho Inventory\n\nSKILLS\nProduct strategy, roadmapping, user research, SQL (intermediate), Amplitude, Mixpanel, Jira, Figma, A/B testing, OKRs, stakeholder management, people management\n\nEDUCATION\nMBA \u2014 INSEAD (2016\u20132017)\nBSc Business Administration \u2014 University of Ghana (2012\u20132016)", "raw_linkedin": "Product leader with seven years in B2B SaaS, specialising in procurement and workflow automation software. Currently at Coupa Software leading the supplier management product with a team of three PMs. I've spent my career building products that enterprise buyers actually adopt \u2014 which means obsessing over the onboarding experience and the moments where value becomes tangible. Remote-first advocate; I've worked fully distributed for four years across multiple time zones. I'm a strong believer in data-informed (not data-dictated) decisions. Open to senior PM or Head of Product roles at growth-stage B2B SaaS companies. Based in Accra, Ghana \u2014 UK or US visa sponsorship needed.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Welcome, Amara. Can you walk me through a product you're most proud of?\n\nAmara: The supplier onboarding redesign at Coupa. When I joined, the onboarding completion rate was around 45% \u2014 suppliers were dropping off because the flow was too complex and the value wasn't clear early enough. I ran discovery with 20+ suppliers, identified the three biggest friction points, and shipped a redesigned flow over two quarters. Completion rate went to 80%. That project also strengthened my relationship with the enterprise sales team because it directly reduced their escalations.\n\nInterviewer: How do you manage your PM team?\n\nAmara: I have three direct reports at Coupa. I try to give them real ownership \u2014 they own their areas fully and I'm there to unblock, coach, and set context. I do weekly 1:1s and we do a monthly team retrospective.\n\nInterviewer: What are your thoughts on the remote setup here? We're fully async-first.\n\nAmara: Perfect for me. I've been fully remote for four years and I'm very comfortable with async communication. I'm in the GMT+0 zone, which works well for overlap with UK and European teams.\n\nInterviewer: And visa? We do offer sponsorship.\n\nAmara: Yes, I'd need a UK Global Talent or Skilled Worker visa. I've checked the requirements and I believe I qualify based on my experience. That's great that you offer sponsorship.\n\nInterviewer: Salary expectations?\n\nAmara: I'm currently earning the equivalent of \u00a388,000. I'd be looking for \u00a390\u201395,000 for this step up in seniority and location context.", "years_experience": 7.0, "skills": ["Product strategy", "Roadmapping", "User research", "SQL (intermediate)", "Amplitude", "Mixpanel", "Jira", "Figma", "A/B testing", "OKRs", "Stakeholder management", "People management", "Data-informed decision making", "Enterprise sales alignment"], "industries": ["B2B SaaS", "Enterprise software", "Procurement software", "Workflow automation"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.88, "constraints": [{"id": "72ada70f", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "Requires UK Global Talent or Skilled Worker visa sponsorship", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship_required", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "758c9152", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Currently based in Accra, Ghana; requires relocation to UK or US", "canonical_key": "office_location", "value": "UK or US", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": null}, {"id": "a195ce2b", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Strong preference for remote-first or fully remote roles; has 4 years remote experience", "canonical_key": "remote_work", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "35bfb0f5", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Currently earning equivalent of \u00a388,000", "canonical_key": "salary_current", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "2c7ce242", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation \u00a390,000 for this step up in seniority and location context", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "d69fa2b1", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Target salary range \u00a390\u201395,000 for senior role with location move", "canonical_key": "salary_target", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "4d7e29d8", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Comfortable and prefers async-first communication; currently works across multiple time zones", "canonical_key": "async_communication", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "18438d8e", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Open to senior PM or Head of Product roles", "canonical_key": "seniority_level_preference", "value": "senior PM or Head of Product", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "200fa9fa", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry", "description": "Preference for growth-stage B2B SaaS companies", "canonical_key": "company_stage_preference", "value": "growth-stage B2B SaaS", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.87, "currency": null}, {"id": "1766cb85", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "timezone", "description": "Based in GMT+0 timezone (Accra); comfortable with UK and European team overlap", "canonical_key": "timezone_preference", "value": "GMT+0", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}], "discipline": "other"}, "embedding": [-0.0006847381591796875, 0.01160430908203125, 0.04339599609375, 0.0185089111328125, -0.03289794921875, 0.027008056640625, 0.0163726806640625, 0.045318603515625, 0.003582000732421875, 0.01189422607421875, 0.00783538818359375, -0.062744140625, -0.00669097900390625, -0.0288543701171875, 